CADANG-CADANG DISEASE, COCONUT PALM - PHILIPPINES: (CAMARINES NORTE) UPDATE
***************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 23 Feb 2012
Source: Philippine Information Agency [edited]
http://www.pia.gov.ph/news/index.php?article=871329807294


The Philippine Coconut Authority (PCA) has commenced a comprehensive survey on Cadang-cadang disease in coconut in Camarines Norte.

PCA Camarines Norte's Editah P. Idnani said that the province and other provinces in Bicol region as well as in Region IV-A and Region VII are affected by the Cadang-cadang viroid infestation based on the yearly monitoring conducted by the PCA - Albay Research Center.

Under the Cadang-cadang Containment and Rehabilitation program, PCA targets to eliminate Cadang-cadang disease in coconuts not only in this province but also in other provinces in the regions cited.

Some 100 000 hectares of land planted with coconut will be under surveillance. The ground survey is being conducted by enumerators in all the 12 municipalities in the province.

[Byline: Rosalita B Manlangit]

